<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 08 at 4:54PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Walton and north
central Newton Counties through 530 PM EDT...
At 454 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Monroe, moving
southeast at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Loganville, Walnut Grove, Between, Good Hope, Jersey,
Windsor, Nicholasville, Youth, Pannell, Campton, Herndonville, Gratis
and Gum Creek.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
